                "Description": "What if a building could breathe? In the middle of Jaipur, Hawa Mahal does exactly that—pulling in air, pushing out heat and turning architecture into a quiet science experiment. It's less a palace, more a perfectly timed exhale. And yes, it really does live up to its name: the 'Palace of Winds.'",
