        "MediaContent": {
            "ImageContent": {
                "Description": "Not all wildlife moments are dramatic—some unfold in perfect stillness. The grey seal resting on the shores of the Orkney Islands, Scotland, is a perfect example. Grey seals are among the UK's largest native marine mammals, with the country supporting around 40% of the world's population. Despite their size, they are remarkably adaptable sleepers. Rather than settling into one long stretch, grey seals nap in short, flexible bursts shaped by their surroundings.",
                "Image": {
                    "Url": "/th?id=OHR.NappingSeal_ROW2198134616_1920x1080.webp",
