            "ImageContent": {
                "Description": "When romance calls, this bird lifts one bright blue foot, then the other, like it's auditioning for a talent show with very strict colour rules. Not metaphorically. Literally. Meet the blue-footed booby. Widely associated with the Galápagos Islands, these seabirds range across the eastern tropical Pacific.",
