        "bot": 1,
        "hs": [],
        "MediaContent": {
            "ImageContent": {
                "Description": "He may be young, but these antlers speak of future battles. In Denali National Park, in Alaska, United States, a young bull moose lifts his head above the shrubs. At this stage, his antlers are more crown than weapon—still covered in velvet. But even now, they hint at a life shaped by instinct, sparring and the quiet pull of dominance.",
                "Image": {
                    "Url": "/th?id=OHR.YoungMoose_ROW0217187286_1920x1080.webp",
