            "ImageContent": {
                "Description": "Nestled in the northern Gulf Coast of Florida in the United States is Rainbow Springs State Park. This area has served as a natural resource for humans and animals for centuries, with the crystal-clear Rainbow River—flowing through the park—playing a major role. The gently winding waterway is fed by Rainbow Springs, one of Florida's largest springs. The water that bubbles up here comes from an almost 200,000-hectare area and eventually flows into the Withlacoochee River.",
                "Image": {
                    "Url": "/th?id=OHR.RainbowRiver_ROW4765713461_1920x1080.webp",
