        "bot": 1,
        "hs": [],
        "MediaContent": {
            "ImageContent": {
                "Description": "Don't let the name fool you—this frog isn't just leafing around. The splendid leaf frog, or splendid treefrog, is a rainforest resident with a flair for the dramatic: neon legs, sticky feet and a disappearing act. One minute it's a humble green leaf, the next it's a flash of colour mid-leap, startling predators. This frog lives high in the canopies of Central and South America, especially in Costa Rica, Panama and parts of Ecuador and Colombia.",
                "Image": {
                    "Url": "/th?id=OHR.SplendidFrog_ROW3619803881_1920x1080.webp",
                    "Wallpaper": "/th?id=OHR.SplendidFrog_ROW3619803881_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg",
