        "MediaContent": {
            "ImageContent": {
                "Description": "Masai giraffes, known for their distinctive jagged blotches, are native to East Africa. Besides Kenya and Uganda, they roam the vast plains of Tanzania's Serengeti, a name derived from the Maasai word 'seringit,' meaning 'endless plains.' Masai giraffes were named after Herr von Tippelskirch, a member of a German scientific expedition who was the first to collect information and specimens of this giraffe subspecies and bring them to Europe.",
                "Image": {
                    "Url": "/th?id=OHR.SerengetiGiraffe_ROW5363450229_1920x1080.webp",
